Happy Birthday to the love of my life @reetu52595
I know m late but u know how much I love u which no post could ever justify.

I don’t say this often, but I want you to know how deeply grateful I am to have you in my life. You’re not just my sister, you’re my heart, my biggest comfort, and my constant strength.

You’ve seen me in my lowest moments, when I felt like giving up, and you’ve silently stood by me, giving me love without even needing to say a word. You’ve understood things I couldn’t explain, and loved me through things I couldn’t admit to anyone else.

Every little thing you’ve done for me, your support, your patience, your way of making me feel safe, I carry all of it with me every single day. You’ve been my reason to smile when I felt broken, and my reminder to keep going when I felt lost.

I don’t know what I did to deserve you, but I thank the universe every day for blessing me with you. You make life feel lighter, warmer, and so much more meaningful.

Happy Birthday my lifeline. I love you more than words could ever hold. You’ll always be my home. 👭❤️

#happybirthday #birthday #birthdaygirl

Sometimes, I just need to find a quiet little corner and sit there—no plans, no rushing, no trying to fix everything all at once. I am someone who is obsessed with taking controls.

It’s crazy how when I stop trying so hard to control every little thing, life starts doing its own thing—and honestly, it’s kind of beautiful. That’s when I remind myself to trust God’s timing, even when I don’t fully understand the path ahead.

I’m learning that some of the best magic happens when I simply let go and let things flow. When I stop pushing, stop stressing, and allow space for miracles. Because He’s always working, even when I can’t see it yet.

So today, I’m sitting back and watching life happen. I’m believing that everything is falling perfectly into place, exactly when it’s supposed to. And honestly, That feels like peace.

#JustBreathe #LetLifeHappen #TrustGodsPlan #FindingPeace #FaithInTheJourney
